com.badlogic.gdx.ai.pfa

Class PathFinderRequest<N>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.badlogic.gdx.ai.pfa.PathFinderRequest<N>
  • Type Parameters:
    N - Type of node

    public class PathFinderRequest<N>
extends java.lang.Object
    A request for interruptible pathfinding that should be sent to a PathFinderQueue through a Telegram.

      • initializeSearch

        public boolean initializeSearch(long timeToRun)
        Interruptible method called by the PathFinderRequestControl as soon as this request starts to be served.
        Parameters:
        timeToRun - the time in nanoseconds that this call can use on the current frame
        Returns:
        true if initialization has completed; false if more time is needed to complete.

      • search

        public boolean search(PathFinder<N> pathFinder,
                      long timeToRun)
        Parameters:
        pathFinder - the path finder
        timeToRun - the time in nanoseconds that this call can use on the current frame
        Returns:
        true if the search has completed; false if more time is needed to complete.

      • finalizeSearch

        public boolean finalizeSearch(long timeToRun)
        Interruptible method called by PathFinderQueue when the path finder has completed the search. You have to check the pathFound field of this request to know if a path has been found.
        Parameters:
        timeToRun - the time in nanoseconds that this call can use on the current frame
        Returns:
        true if finalization has completed; false if more time is needed to complete.
